KITpro OS is a custom Linux distribution based on Rocky Linux.

The base operating system components are derived from Rocky Linux, which itself is rebuilt from sources freely provided by Red Hat, Inc. These components retain their original open-source licenses (e.g., GPLv2, LGPL, BSD, MIT, etc.).

All original content in this repository — including but not limited to kickstart files, shell scripts, branding assets, themes, and RPM spec files — is licensed under the MIT License (see LICENSE).

Rocky Linux is a trademark of the Rocky Enterprise Software Foundation. This project is independent and not officially affiliated with RESF or Red Hat, Inc.